I was very disappointed by all means. Very small space, nothing looking like French, i was hoping to see some French vibes. There were only maybe 4 options to choose from, so very limited menu. Madelleines did not taste right, the ones at Trader Joe ‘s are much better. I really cannot see any reason why to go to this place. One interesting observation was that they were wiping tables and seats with clorox, although good for hygiene, smell was so strong, i felt like would i wanna eat something in a newly cleaned bathroom, really, you want a chocolate/croissant scent in a French cafe..

The service was the only good thing about this place. The tarts, however, were a complete disappointment. I tried three different kinds, and every single one was bland, stale, and lacking any real flavor. Honestly, I’ve had better desserts from a grocery store. Definitely not worth the hype or the price. Won’t be coming back
I like their desserts. Charlotte should have more places like this.All Eastern European vibes at once
Always a clean space, very delicious and beautifully presented desserts, great coffee, and friendly staff.

Chez Marie is a pretty solid French Patisserie. I got the opportunity to taste a large variety of the pastries they were selling that day and was impressed for the most part. The mixed berry entremet was my favorite thing that I tried: it was tart, light, and rich at the same time, while not being overly sweet. The chocolate entremet, while having a pretty presentation, was way too rich and was difficult to eat more than a couple of nibbles. The lemon tart was also pretty with the toasted meringue on it, however, it tasted a little too much like a key lime pie to me. All of the macaroons that I tried were good as well, with standouts being the raspberry and pistachio. The location is very nice in South Park near the OG Pancake House and has a pretty, delicate interior. The ladies working the front were also very nice. It seems they change what they are selling often, I will have to go back and check it out again sometime.
Pretty limited option and they were out of quite a few things by 12:30 on a weekday.

A great spot to feel like you’ve traveled outside of the states! Great atmosphere, beautiful and delicious pastries and coffee, and clean 👌 We ordered the pistachio French best, Black Forest emberet, and a vanilla latte. Everything was excellent! We came on a Sunday around 11am and we were able to get a table. Some weekends may be busier, but honestly we felt like it would be worth the wait ☺️
Fresh! Delicious. 😋 great taste.
The mixed berry danish was very hard, same as a few macaroons. Other than that, enjoyable and nice service.

This is a beautiful little bakery. They make great pastries, the closest I found in Charlotte to the real French ones. They used to make great croissants and pain au chocolat but lately they changed the recipe, I would say skip them and get the pastries.
They offer an array of drink options.
This spot is good hangout place for small groups (4). It is a small place that gets filled up quickly specially on weekends. The parking is free but can be tricky at times as this place is located in a small shopping area with other restaurants and a couple of stores - so plan accordingly.
Overall cute little place with good quality baked goods. Do try it!
The pastries are delicious!!

Definitely was not expecting this!   Traveling from far away seen this advertised from IG influencer. Everything looked great.  Surprised at how small it was inside.  I got a Togo order and there were not many option’s. One of the waitresses made a comment to another with an eye roll when an eat in customer asked for more water for her tea. I was flabbergasted by the prices of such small desserts, which now a days norm-  just is not expensive. The flavor of the desserts was not really that great. Mediocre at best. Will not go back.

I found hair in my cappuccino. It was curly, and my hair is straight. I felt sick when I got home. It was disgusting, especially since I was almost done drinking it.
A very nice  france café in Charlotte with very good cakes.

This pastry shop is a small gem! Tucked in a shopping center right across from Southpark Mall. Perfect for a sweet or savory treat after shopping. There are a lot of stores so parking can be a little crowded. I ordered a cheese danish, croissant, and a tiramisu macaron. Everything was fresh. My favorite was the cheese danish..it was the best danish I’ve had. Buttery, flaky, perfect cheese to pastry ratio. Definitely will visit again. Price tag $13 not including tip.

What an amazing little shop! I have a friend who keeps talking abt them so I finally got my chance to check it out. It’s very small and intimate in there and not much seating but fortunately we were able to find some once a group left. I ordered the London fog, smoked ham sandwich and a cheese danish. Everything was positivity delish. That danish was literally the best I’ve ever had. This place is definitely a must try, and believe me I will be back over and over again.
Very cute place and good croissants, pastries & drinks
Great coffee, real fresh baguettes, and a wonderful ambience.

Nice place, but a bit small, so it gets crowded. Food and drinks were delicious. My chai latte was spot on - the right amount of sweetness. Staff was friendly and polite. A good experience, will come again.

I was very excited to go there to eat, I read several reviews of the place and it is just as described, a very nice atmosphere and good customer service and the food was delicious, I hope to go there again with my friends!
The place is very nice,even though I did not stay.The Pastries are very good.

Great place! I recently had the pleasure of dining at Chez Marie Patisserie, and it was a delightful experience! The moment I walked in, I was greeted by the heavenly aroma of freshly baked goods and the charming, cozy atmosphere. I started with a buttery croissant that was perfectly flaky and golden. For dessert, I couldn’t resist trying their signature macarons, which were exquisite—soft, colorful, and filled with rich flavors. I also enjoyed a slice of their decadent chocolate cake, which was rich and moist, a true indulgence. The staff were friendly and knowledgeable, eager to help with recommendations. Overall, Chez Marie Patisserie is a must-visit for anyone with a sweet tooth or looking for a cozy spot to enjoy delicious pastries. I can't wait to go back and try more of their delectable treats!

reviews_data.review_text: I went for a little afternoon snack and coffee. Everything was delicious. Nice place. All the pastries were very fresh and delicious. The cappuccino was perfect as well as the blue matcha.

We were really excited this visit this place.  We did not realize It was located in a very crowded shopping plaza, so the parking lot was almost full.  There is a front patio to sit on which was great because we had our dog with us.  My hubby ordered for us and I really wanted the Cheese Danish but they were sold out.  So we picked 2 different desserts and coffee.

The desserts were good, kind of sweet for me but the presentation was beautiful.  The coffee was ok, it seemed like more foam than coffee.  Again, I loved the presentation of the coffee.

The service was great and the waitress was very kind.  The price was a little expensive for 2 desserts and 2 coffees.  With a tip it was $32.00.

Everything I tried was absolutely delicious, and the coffee was fantastic too. This bakery truly feels like a little slice of Paris, and I can’t wait to come back. Highly recommend

reviews_data.review_text: I ended up only ordering 2 pastries to go as they are very expensive for their size. It's very small, the glaze was rubbery, the filling was sparce, split, and curdled. For $8 I'm surprised they put them out like that. reviews_data.owner_answer:
We are sorry you were dissatisfied with your experience at Chez Marie.

We believe that the value of our products that we offer is fairly estimated and it corresponds to the high quality of the ingredients we select and hard work we apply. 

We agree with your comment about the design on the latte, but we are currently training new people. We can reassure you that the quality of the drink remains the same as all of our baristas follow the same recipe. 

We wanted to make it right to you and served you a freshly made cappuccino upon your request free of charge, that you have also asked to be taken “to go”.

We make all our desserts daily and due to a high demand we run out of many items by the end of the day. Our customers can always call and place an advance order for a later pick up.

reviews_data.review_text: Good service and gluten free options. Quaint place. They bake the goods on-site. Slightly pricey, but as to be expected based on the location.

This patisserie never disappoints. The desserts are not only gorgeous, but also delicious!
Keep in mind it is a small place, and can be busy. Also, it is pricier than other patisseries around, but definitely worth it.

Food and service were great, the employees were super friendly but my partner and I had a very uncomfortable experience with the owner sitting in the cafe. When my partner put cash in the tip jar, she piped up in a snooty tone and said, “You know you don’t have to do that, this isn’t like a restaurant.”
It’s clear to me that the owner doesn’t think her employees deserve tips and as a hospitality employee and former barista, that indicates that she doesn’t care about her employees being recognized for delivering good service. There is no way she’s paying her employees enough that they wouldn’t appreciate a tip.
We would return for the food and service but would rather not put money in her pocket.

I didn't try more because I thought it was a little pricey. The vibe was nice enough; not sure if it was more the staff, the inside guests, or both but there was a hint of being standoff-ish. Not sure I would return.

Cons: I saw a post of Chez Marie on Instagram and came here very excited to try it out, unfortunately it was a disappointment. reviews_data.review_text: This is a very cute place and the pastries are really beautiful. I think the aesthetics and where it’s located is why it could be popular. The taste is just not there, in my opinion. Also, luxury doesn’t excuse the amount of waste that’s going on here. They were packing each of these items in the picture in a separate plastic container or baggy. Each item is also served on a hard plastic piece (that if I could’ve asked for without I would have). I asked for items to just be placed in one box. They still gave me two boxes and a bag with the macrons in it. They were afraid they’d move around and get ruined and that the box wouldn’t close over the lavender cake. Get boxes that are taller since you make items this tall and each of these hard plastic pieces can have icing placed on the bottom to keep them in place. It was done on two items in the box and not on another that was placed in a separate box. Be more concerned with what you’re putting out into the environment. It’s at an egregious level.

I wanted to write a review since I have entered Chez Marie in Sharon Corners. I would like to thank Mrs. Maria Siragusa and her husband, Mr. Siragusa so much for their hospitality and generosity when visiting this past Wednesday.

Blake and I had a wonderful time and getting to meet Mrs. Siragusa as well as receiving the service from the lovely staff added extra sweetness to our sugar overload that day.

To Mrs. Siragusa, thank you for being so kind and patient w/ explaining the desserts as well as encouraging me to step out my comfort zone and try the blue cheese macaron. And yes, you win. A savory confection that is worth a try. But I have to say the mango and raspberry rose are my favorite. The best raspberry macaron I have tried to date. Ladurée & Pierre Hermé Paris in France did not come close to that raspberry rose.

Your passion and love are sure reflected in your desserts and can also be seen in your staff. Its really that contagious. The good kind of course. I would like to highlight the gentleman that made our coffees. His customer service was just amazing and went above and beyond to ensure we were taken care of while we dined and was just overall a sincere, kind gem.

Having a background in the service/restaurant industry, specifically in full scale restaurants, I have never received the love, respect, and kindness in a facility let alone in an owner or manager.

In a world that is currently being clouded with negativity and uncertainty, you are such a light and positivity and a great asset to have in SouthPark. I strive now more than ever to acknowledge individuals that deserve to be praised. With that being said, I wish you every little piece of success and happiness that comes your way. It is so much more than the sourdough sandwiches, lattes, croissant, macarons, lemon basil tart w/ toast meringue, & the mousse entremet. (Yes, it was devoured between Blake and I only, and yes, we ate ALL of it with no regrets)

Thank you again for the experience. Will visit again real soon.

-Christine

We still have a lot of room to grow in every aspect of our business but we are passionate about it and this is exactly what pushes us to go further and grow. We can’t wait to see you again at Chez Marie! Have a wonderful rest of the weekend!

Chez Marie is a pretty solid French Patisserie. I got the opportunity to taste a large variety of the pastries they were selling that day and was impressed for the most part. The mixed berry entremet was my favorite thing that I tried: it was tart, light, and rich at the same time, while not being overly sweet. The chocolate entremet, while having a pretty presentation, was way too rich and was difficult to eat more than a couple of nibbles. The lemon tart was also pretty with the toasted meringue on it, however, it tasted a little too much like a key lime pie to me. All of the macaroons that I tried were good as well, with standouts being the raspberry and pistachio. The location is very nice in South Park near the OG Pancake House and has a pretty, delicate interior. The ladies working the front were also very nice. It seems they change what they are selling often, I will have to go back and check it out again sometime.

A great spot to feel like you’ve traveled outside of the states! Great atmosphere, beautiful and delicious pastries and coffee, and clean 👌 We ordered the pistachio French best, Black Forest emberet, and a vanilla latte. Everything was excellent! We came on a Sunday around 11am and we were able to get a table. Some weekends may be busier, but honestly we felt like it would be worth the wait ☺️
Fresh! Delicious. 😋 great taste.
The mixed berry danish was very hard, same as a few macaroons. Other than that, enjoyable and nice service.

This is a beautiful little bakery. They make great pastries, the closest I found in Charlotte to the real French ones. They used to make great croissants and pain au chocolat but lately they changed the recipe, I would say skip them and get the pastries.
They offer an array of drink options.
This spot is good hangout place for small groups (4). It is a small place that gets filled up quickly specially on weekends. The parking is free but can be tricky at times as this place is located in a small shopping area with other restaurants and a couple of stores - so plan accordingly.
Overall cute little place with good quality baked goods. Do try it!
The pastries are delicious!!

Definitely was not expecting this!   Traveling from far away seen this advertised from IG influencer. Everything looked great.  Surprised at how small it was inside.  I got a Togo order and there were not many option’s. One of the waitresses made a comment to another with an eye roll when an eat in customer asked for more water for her tea. I was flabbergasted by the prices of such small desserts, which now a days norm-  just is not expensive. The flavor of the desserts was not really that great. Mediocre at best. Will not go back.

I found hair in my cappuccino. It was curly, and my hair is straight. I felt sick when I got home. It was disgusting, especially since I was almost done drinking it.
A very nice  france café in Charlotte with very good cakes.

This pastry shop is a small gem! Tucked in a shopping center right across from Southpark Mall. Perfect for a sweet or savory treat after shopping. There are a lot of stores so parking can be a little crowded. I ordered a cheese danish, croissant, and a tiramisu macaron. Everything was fresh. My favorite was the cheese danish..it was the best danish I’ve had. Buttery, flaky, perfect cheese to pastry ratio. Definitely will visit again. Price tag $13 not including tip.

What an amazing little shop! I have a friend who keeps talking abt them so I finally got my chance to check it out. It’s very small and intimate in there and not much seating but fortunately we were able to find some once a group left. I ordered the London fog, smoked ham sandwich and a cheese danish. Everything was positivity delish. That danish was literally the best I’ve ever had. This place is definitely a must try, and believe me I will be back over and over again.
Very cute place and good croissants, pastries & drinks
Great coffee, real fresh baguettes, and a wonderful ambience.

Nice place, but a bit small, so it gets crowded. Food and drinks were delicious. My chai latte was spot on - the right amount of sweetness. Staff was friendly and polite. A good experience, will come again.

I was very excited to go there to eat, I read several reviews of the place and it is just as described, a very nice atmosphere and good customer service and the food was delicious, I hope to go there again with my friends!
The place is very nice,even though I did not stay.The Pastries are very good.

Great place! I recently had the pleasure of dining at Chez Marie Patisserie, and it was a delightful experience! The moment I walked in, I was greeted by the heavenly aroma of freshly baked goods and the charming, cozy atmosphere. I started with a buttery croissant that was perfectly flaky and golden. For dessert, I couldn’t resist trying their signature macarons, which were exquisite—soft, colorful, and filled with rich flavors. I also enjoyed a slice of their decadent chocolate cake, which was rich and moist, a true indulgence. The staff were friendly and knowledgeable, eager to help with recommendations. Overall, Chez Marie Patisserie is a must-visit for anyone with a sweet tooth or looking for a cozy spot to enjoy delicious pastries. I can't wait to go back and try more of their delectable treats!

reviews_data.review_text: I went for a little afternoon snack and coffee. Everything was delicious. Nice place. All the pastries were very fresh and delicious. The cappuccino was perfect as well as the blue matcha.
Very tasty cute place .

We were really excited this visit this place.  We did not realize It was located in a very crowded shopping plaza, so the parking lot was almost full.  There is a front patio to sit on which was great because we had our dog with us.  My hubby ordered for us and I really wanted the Cheese Danish but they were sold out.  So we picked 2 different desserts and coffee.

The desserts were good, kind of sweet for me but the presentation was beautiful.  The coffee was ok, it seemed like more foam than coffee.  Again, I loved the presentation of the coffee.

The service was great and the waitress was very kind.  The price was a little expensive for 2 desserts and 2 coffees.  With a tip it was $32.00.

Sitting on the patio was nothing fancy as you are looking at a bunch of cars in a parking lot.

I am glad we visited this place as it’s always nice to try new places.

I almost don’t want to write this review because this place is such a gem—I’d hate to see it get too crowded! But honestly, the croissants here are incredible—as authentic as any I’ve had in France. Everything I tried was absolutely delicious, and the coffee was fantastic too. This bakery truly feels like a little slice of Paris, and I can’t wait to come back. Highly recommend
Love this cute bakery.  Comfy seating, hand made coffee drinks, baked goods, some light food.  We didn’t try the food but got desserts, macarons, and a latte.  All tasty and good service.

This place is amazing! I am amazed every time! The pastry they make! Not only look amazing but taste JUST AS GOOD! The best latte I have had in charlotte to date! The actually know how to foam milk properly and its perfect! ITs always a treat to go here! You MUST TRY!
Croissants don't look very good.  Entremets look okay but not interesting.  Service is slow.

This place is very cozy, we tried the
passion fruit macaroons and I recommend the raspberry ones.
The eclair has raspberry filling, delicious.
The almond croissant is very tasty, and the cheese and berry Danish tasted like any other. We ordered cappuccino with whole milk and oat milk and they were delicious.

👌🏻👌🏻
We visited this cafe every day, but today we were served disgustingly... As if they didn't notice and served us poorly at the checkout. It's a pity, but I won't go to this cafe again

Loved the atmosphere! Fresh and delicious bakery and desserts 🍨
Crepes and sandwiches are European “style”. Not huge size portions but perfect so that you can eat a dessert after your “main” meal.
Would definitely come back to try more bakery items.

This is an amazing find in Charlotte.
Congratulations Maria!!!
The Croissant's are excellent!!
Looking forward to trying the tarts next....

In which I did, "the Lemon meringue Tart" It maybe one of the best things I ever ate!!!  Amazing!
The macchiato was excellent.
The atmosphere is perfect!
The cappuccino, perfect!

reviews_data.review_text: I ended up only ordering 2 pastries to go as they are very expensive for their size. The lychee raspberry entremet was fantastic, and each layer was a delight and perfectly made. I would come back for another. The earl grey eclair however was a huge disappointment. It's very small, the glaze was rubbery, the filling was sparce, split, and curdled. For $8 I'm surprised they put them out like that. They really need to adjust their prices on some things or rework them to make them worth it.
Delicious desserts and tea. Coffee tastes burnt, definitely not getting coffee anymore. Great selections on desserts though.
Really cute environment and GREAT French pastries. The latte was amazing as well and the Cafe has a cute little gift section!

Excellent sourdough sandwiches, and the fresh pastries are wondrous. My wife and I greatly enjoyed lunch. By the way, I was not the only guy there. The space is attractive, and the service is friendly but attentive. We’ll be back often.
Wonderful little spot- the crepe and coffee were delicious!! We had some pastries to go and everything including the service was wonderful.
Fabulous place. Everything was amazing

The croissant was very dry, no color pale looking and also hardly any butter in it.
Will not be coming back
Beautiful cafe selling exceptional French pastries. Prices were steep but we felt it was reflected in the quality of the ingredients.

Just purchased an almond croissant. I couldn’t help but wonder if it was simply a left over butter croissant from the day before, cut with a touch of almond something inside. Extremely dry. Like stale?! I’m  not sure how this was served or deemed acceptable to serve. A clear winner as the worst almond croissant I’ve ever had. Very disappointed. The pastries looked pretty.

This place was absolutely amazing. Their pastry display was so beautiful. It made me want to try them all. The Lavender Eclair and Blue Matcha Latte was beyond amazing. I need to go back and try their coffee but the Matcha Latte was on point. They also have sandwiches but my wife and I really wanted to try their pastries.

This place is so good and so cute. Nice tables, chairs l, atmosphere and food!!! The coffee was so good and the sourdough bread is on the low gluten level for sensitivity so it did well with my belly!!! All of their pastries are amazing! You can tell they put there heart into this place!!!!
Pastries are alright,
Great for a little french Cafe.

Everything they have is absolutely 💯 perfect!
My favorite place if I want to feel fancy and eat a good treat, coffee is perfect also. They know what they are doing. Music and interior are also beautiful,  just wish it was a little bit bigger or different location, because sometimes it is hard to find parking or a seat, and if all seats are taken, you feel like people at the other table are sitting with you lol so need more space for sure.

reviews_data.review_text: We ordered some pastries, sandwiches, and Blue Matcha latte (visited here in April). Some of the pastries are so good. But some of it had less flavor. And the Chez Marie sandwich was so good 👍 The ingredients were really fresh, and baguette bread was fantastic! ( a little bit hard, though). And the Blue Matcha Latte..  hmm.. maybe I had too much expectations. The lack of matcha flavor made me disappointed. I will try other beverages next time :)
Nice place
I enjoyed trying a delicious pistachio eclair and the attention of their staff was incredible, I really recommend visiting them.😉
Súper el servicio y los postres deliciosos súper ricos súper recomendable
Best place for breakfast or just to drink a coffee with a perfect dessert
Such a cute coffee shop which brings in the feel of French everywhere… loved it
Terrible food.  Messed up orders in store and take out.  First time in the location.  There are two other French bakeries/eateries nearby which are 10 times better.  Food is ordinary.

The pastries were amazing!! I would definitely go again for those! The crepes sounded amazing, but were a let down. The visual appeal was incredible with everything!! Very pleasing to the eye. The Blue Chai and cappuccino were good!

Food is okay but first order of the morning
and they did not get it right. I was stiffed of the right amount of pastries but charged accordingly and did not realized until I arrived home.
Everything was really tasty and the service was exceptionally welcoming.

Delicious!

First time visiting the bakery. It’s a small, quaint shop with limited seating. The croissant was delicious!

The service was good and there is plenty of parking.

We ordered sandwiches and eclairs.

only taking away one start because the prices should  be lowered by at least 15%… one eclair is 7/8 dollars
A Beautiful Experience!
Make a reservation for afternoon tea. It was truly a wonderful experience, and the pastries and tea sandwiches were amazing.
It's evident the staff cares to provide a good service. The food was amazing and the place is so CUTE
Taste is top notch.. ambiance is nice.. tried hot chocolate and 3 pastries all are yummy
The coconut lime palova was delicious

If you want unprofessional and no customer service, visit this place. Everyone I encountered was very rude. The cashier had an attitude while I was ordering. When I asked to provide the gold pastry holder they refused. The pastries are overpriced and not good, there’s limited space, and the coffee is better at other places. If I can give a zero as a rating I would.
Me encanta su atención!
Everything was so delicious,Everything looks super clean, and costumer service is excellent

Finally a proper cafe in Charlotte! Small, quaint, great to sip a cappuccino in the morning and read a book. After living in Italy for eight years I surely missed a good espresso and these guys have nailed it.
Excellent attention. I loved the macaroni and coffee.
Few times already found a black hair in my pastry 🤧
Matcha bad. Dont get. Didnt get serviced for 5 mins at register. 19 bucks gone :(

Quite “a find” tucked away in an obscure retail-oriented corner of SouthPark. French flair and panache that transports me back to my haunts and halcyon days on the Left Bank of Paris. The best part is that the food is top notch. But just keep this a secret, por favor.

Some of the pastries were delicious. I chose a selection of different ones to try, and some were better than others. The espresso mouse tart was good. The carrot cake was ok. Overall, the coffee was good, and the atmosphere was nice. It is very busy on a Sunday brunch. I was a little disappointed that the pastries weren't as fresh, especially for the prices.
This place has some interesting tasting coffee. I love the flavor. It was open I would have went over there but it's late Sunday. And I had to go over to the fake McDonald's just down the street.

Very expensive for the product. Everything has an excellent presentation and the desserts are good but too expensive. The caramel coffee was terrible and the chai latte tasted like hot milk with cinnamon.

Me and my girlfriend went in today and bought a latte, a chai, and one pastry. The total was ~$28 after a 20% tip. Long story short, we never received the pastry and when we went up asked, they said we never ordered it despite having a receipt for $28. They had us pay for another pastry. I would not recommend this place to anyone—poorest service and customer experience I’ve ever had at a coffee shop.

We preordered through phone because we had a 2hr drive and we brought all the sweets for our family and we all enjoyed every dessert. Thank you for that experience. We will definitely be back for tea time with all our girls

I went with my sister and niece for Tea Time. Yummy sandwiches and out of this world hot tea service. So Old World vibe meets modern shopping.

Super cute place , friendly service and delicious French bakery good's.

Go for coffee or tea with treats, you won't be disappointed..

reviews_data.owner_answer:
We are sorry you were dissatisfied with your experience at Chez Marie.

We believe that the value of our products that we offer is fairly estimated and it corresponds to the high quality of the ingredients we select and hard work we apply. 

We agree with your comment about the design on the latte, but we are currently training new people. We can reassure you that the quality of the drink remains the same as all of our baristas follow the same recipe. 

We wanted to make it right to you and served you a freshly made cappuccino upon your request free of charge, that you have also asked to be taken “to go”.

We make all our desserts daily and due to a high demand we run out of many items by the end of the day. Our customers can always call and place an advance order for a later pick up.

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious coffee made from beans roasted by Bristot in the Dolomites. The carrot cake was also delicious. Don't waste $7 on the baguette. No crust, very flabby, only good for toast.

Ohh la la. French and Fresh. I loved the intimate bright location. Gorgeous decor with vibrant esthetic.

I got the Blue Mattcha w/ Stevia (Iced). It's made with Lavender, and it's Sligh sweet with a beautiful aromatic.  It doesn't have anything to cut the deep dairy taste. However, I like milk so I wasn't disappointed. There's a borage of pastries to tempt you. I found the display gorgeous. I'm on no carbs right now, but they looked so enchanting.

reviews_data.review_text: Good service and gluten free options. Quaint place. They bake the goods on-site. Slightly pricey, but as to be expected based on the location.

This patisserie never disappoints. The desserts are not only gorgeous, but also delicious!
Keep in mind it is a small place, and can be busy. Also, it is pricier than other patisseries around, but definitely worth it.

Food and service were great, the employees were super friendly but my partner and I had a very uncomfortable experience with the owner sitting in the cafe. When my partner put cash in the tip jar, she piped up in a snooty tone and said, “You know you don’t have to do that, this isn’t like a restaurant.”
It’s clear to me that the owner doesn’t think her employees deserve tips and as a hospitality employee and former barista, that indicates that she doesn’t care about her employees being recognized for delivering good service. There is no way she’s paying her employees enough that they wouldn’t appreciate a tip.
We would return for the food and service but would rather not put money in her pocket.

This review is overdue. I stopped by on Sunday, 02-05-23 while in the area. I ordered the passion fruit tart and the blue cheese pair danish. Both were good. I didn't try more because I thought it was a little pricey. The vibe was nice enough; not sure if it was more the staff, the inside guests, or both but there was a hint of being standoff-ish. Not sure I would return.
Excelente ambiente y el café espectacular al igual que la comida.

It has small seating inside but they do have a lot of tables and chairs outside. When the weather is nice would be perfect to sit outside, even the outside chairs give Paris vibes. Food was really good too!
Really beautiful decor, very Parisian vibe. Food was fresh and priced fairly. We will be back!
A little expensive,but very good testing,they have to do lattes less buble,I didn't have any drink :) I just huuped:)))
This place is so cute! I definitely want to visit again and actually dine-in. I got the Black Forest entremet & chocolate raspberry eclair and they were both superb.
Such a beautiful, French style cafe in Southpark Charlotte NC
The cutest little spot. Incredible service and the food was so good. Will definitely be coming back
Very welcoming, they were willing to stay over to accommodate or service. Very professional and clean. Definitely a place I would come back as a regular.
The latte was good.
Luogo raffinato, ottimo per una pausa caffè.

The patisserie is so beautiful and chic. The minuted we walked in we were greeted and a gentleman explained everything they had on the display.We ordered a coffee tart, pistachio Macaroon and pumpkin spice mousse cake (i guess that's what it was called).We also ordered Blue Matcha with almond milk which was just perfect.Everything was so perfect.I will back to satiate my craving for french dessert soon.
This place is quiant, and the pastry selection is perfect.  The homemade lavender comes close to the superb one at Chrmn Cafe, Elgin, Texas!

One of the best coffee in Charlotte. If you know how should taste good coffee this is a place to get one. As for macaroons unfortunately they were not fresh  :(
We tried another pastries - they were perfect

Pros: The cafe had a lovely atmosphere. The decor was very pretty and it was clean inside.

Cons: I saw a post of Chez Marie on Instagram and came here very excited to try it out, unfortunately it was a disappointment. I tried the Pumpkin Spice dessert and the Spinach and Feta Danish and both were very bland.  I was disappointed on the lack of flavor from both pastries and did not feel like they were worth the price.
We ordered Blue Matcha and Paris Brest and both were amazing. Couldn’t taste the savory stuff as it was very close to their closing time. But overall very good place.

By far The BEST PATISSERIE in Charlotte!!!!! The ingredients are really good and the place was so beautiful, there's outdoor and indoor seating. It's clean and open, love it! This place takes all the little details into consideration, they are not mass produced as some other bakeries. All their choices are delicious and nothing is too sweet that it can't be eaten. They also had a unique option for a decaf flower/tea latte. It was a blue color and tasted pretty good, complimenting the sweets perfectly. After trying all the patisseries in Charlotte this is our favorite and we will be back.
I didn't like the service, the sandwich came wrong, the espresso tasted burnt, I don't like to complain but I really wouldn't go back to this place

The atmosphere of the cafe was far from comfortable, and it felt as if the employees were just gathered there, maintaining an awkward silence throughout the visit. Overall, my experience at this cafe was less than satisfactory, I hope they can work on improving their service and ambiance in the future.

It’s simple at Chez Marie I found a piece of home. I’m from Paris, France and I have lived in the US for 10 years.
I have tried dozen of “French authentic” cafe & such and this one I can tell you is LEGIT !
The atmosphere, the music playing in the background and most importantly the QUALITY of the food was there !
We’ve tried the quiche Lorraine, chocolate croissant, blue cheese/pear danish and I wanted SO MUCH MORE.
Can’t recommend enough & will be back for sure !
A lovely place for your coffee/tea time. Service is ok, but the food and drinks are pretty good

It's a really nice place! Very nice style and unique delicious food.
Prices are good for the quality.
Super cute cafe, very clean. Friendly and fast service. Tasty pastries!

Je l'aime! The space is modern, a bit minimalisic but with a touch of elegance. I tried the passion fruit tart. Parfait! The right amount of sweetness. It was smooth and light. I would definitely go back to try the other pastries.

Chez Marie is a massive upgrade to the space and a welcome addition to SP.  The quality of the pastries is high and we can’t wait to try more things. We started with the 2 Entremets, Berry and Frazier. We also picked up Pain au Chocolate, Blue Cheese Pear Danish, Macarons and a Passion Fruit Tart.  On our next visit we’ll go for lunch and try the sandwiches and salads. CM is off to a great start.

reviews_data.review_text: The best cafe in town. Friendly customer service. I highly recommend everyone to visit this place.I had an afternoon tea.  jasmine is so nice I had a great customer service.

Awe, I was so excited to try this place.  I ordered lunch to go today.  The Crepe Monsieur.  It's my favorite crepe anywhere.  Smoked ham, gruyere, bernaise sauce and a fried egg.  It was soooo disappointing.  I am not sure if they simply forgot, but there was no bernaise and gruyere on it.  It was just egg and ham and was super dry.  Without the sauce or cheese it just had no flavor.  I wish I had taken a picture of the inside but I ended up tossing it and wasting $15.  I hate leaving a bad review but feel like they need the feedback.  The store itself was cute and the service was fast and friendly.  I will likely give them one more try and check the crepe before I leave.  If it's better I will update my review
So delicious

I took the cardamom roll which was tasty! It has a creamy filling with cardamom flavor - more on the sweeter side though. Would love to come back and try new varieties.

Cappuccino is great! We got a bunch of desserts to go.
Bello exquisito única experiencia 😘
Lovely cafe, everything looked pristine inside. The treats I got were delicious but it do is a bit pricey. Staff was very friendly.
Pricey but great
Food was delicious 😋 Especially the atmosphere of the place made us feel like we were in France 🇫🇷
Dessert wasn't fresh

So impressed! I ordered an almond milk latte. The espresso was so smooth and not bitter at all. To eat, I ordered the crepe monsieur. It was topped with a fried egg, sunny side up, that had golden and slightly crisp edges. The yolk was not overly runny. The crepe was a nice balance of savory with a hint of sweetness and the dressing that came with the side salad was also very tasty. I will definitely be coming back.

Excellent coffee shop! I recommend the almond croissant and an oat milk cappuccino with vanilla. It’s always very clean and bright. Only gets busy in the middle of the day Saturday. I love stopping by Chez Marie!

What a lovely cafe! I was drawn in by the stunningly beautiful entremets (multiple flavor layers with gluten free cake, then  covered in a beautiful glaze). They are also available in full sized cakes like the Black Forest cake for my birthday (pictured).  I love to surprise my friends with these awesome tasting beauties. They always bring smiles!

My husband loves the croissants and danishes (sweet or savory) with coffee.  I am in love with the London Fog tea with oat milk and any gluten free treat (I rotate on the flavors).  My goddaughter loves the salads, a chai tea latte and the berry entremets. We love to sit in the fresh inside atmosphere or outdoors on a nice day.

Chez Marie makes my heart feel light. It always feels so cosmopolitan to hear snippets of British, Spanish or French accents. So worth a visit or for takeout!
It was very cute and nice cafe. It was kinda busy even I visit in around 10 AM in Sunday. They have various pastries and breads. Desserts was amazing too!
Came here after watching too much British Baking show. Was not disappointed. Love the tarts. I will keep coming back until my pants don’t fit.
Amazing desserts
A nice french bakery with very good and kind service. Good bread, cookies and pastries.
Very nice and cozy bakery Cafe with a nice choice of pretty and delicious pastries and other desserts.  I really enjoyed my time there with my girlfriends on my birthday.

This was one of the BEST lattes I’ve ever had! I got a vanilla iced oat milk latte & the espresso was so smooth. The girls at the front were super sweet as well. Highly recommend & will be back next time I’m in Charlotte!
Gorgeously cozy cafe. Wi-Fi is extremely fast. The pastries are absolutely beautiful.

Good coffe, tasty deserts & cozy atmosphere

Great patisserie / cafe. Been here several times now. Food is elegantly presented. French music to give the vibe. Taste is spot on - I’ve tried croissant, eclair, and more as well as sandwiches/quiche. All excellent. A bit tucked away but worth looking for. Owners are kind people too.

reviews_data.review_text: This is a very cute place and the pastries are really beautiful. I think the aesthetics and where it’s located is why it could be popular. The taste is just not there, in my opinion. Also, luxury doesn’t excuse the amount of waste that’s going on here. They were packing each of these items in the picture in a separate plastic container or baggy. Each item is also served on a hard plastic piece (that if I could’ve asked for without I would have). I asked for items to just be placed in one box. They still gave me two boxes and a bag with the macrons in it. They were afraid they’d move around and get ruined and that the box wouldn’t close over the lavender cake. Get boxes that are taller since you make items this tall and each of these hard plastic pieces can have icing placed on the bottom to keep them in place. It was done on two items in the box and not on another that was placed in a separate box. Be more concerned with what you’re putting out into the environment. It’s at an egregious level.

I wanted to write a review since I have entered Chez Marie in Sharon Corners. I would like to thank Mrs. Maria Siragusa and her husband, Mr. Siragusa so much for their hospitality and generosity when visiting this past Wednesday.

Blake and I had a wonderful time and getting to meet Mrs. Siragusa as well as receiving the service from the lovely staff added extra sweetness to our sugar overload that day.

To Mrs. Siragusa, thank you for being so kind and patient w/ explaining the desserts as well as encouraging me to step out my comfort zone and try the blue cheese macaron. And yes, you win. A savory confection that is worth a try. But I have to say the mango and raspberry rose are my favorite. The best raspberry macaron I have tried to date. Ladurée & Pierre Hermé Paris in France did not come close to that raspberry rose.

Your passion and love are sure reflected in your desserts and can also be seen in your staff. Its really that contagious. The good kind of course. I would like to highlight the gentleman that made our coffees. His customer service was just amazing and went above and beyond to ensure we were taken care of while we dined and was just overall a sincere, kind gem.

Having a background in the service/restaurant industry, specifically in full scale restaurants, I have never received the love, respect, and kindness in a facility let alone in an owner or manager.

In a world that is currently being clouded with negativity and uncertainty, you are such a light and positivity and a great asset to have in SouthPark. I strive now more than ever to acknowledge individuals that deserve to be praised. With that being said, I wish you every little piece of success and happiness that comes your way. It is so much more than the sourdough sandwiches, lattes, croissant, macarons, lemon basil tart w/ toast meringue, & the mousse entremet. (Yes, it was devoured between Blake and I only, and yes, we ate ALL of it with no regrets)

Thank you again for the experience. Will visit again real soon.

-Christine
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you Christine for such a feedback. We are aompleased and honored to hear that you enjoyed your overall experience. We still have a lot of room to grow in every aspect of our business but we are passionate about it and this is exactly what pushes us to go further and grow. We can’t wait to see you again at Chez Marie! Have a wonderful rest of the weekend!
